{{en-noun}}Objectivism(ŏb-jĕk'tē-vĭzĕm)

1. The act of being objective, i.e. [http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/objectivity objectivity].

2. One of several doctrines in which one believes that all of reality is objective and exists outside of the mind, also that knowledge is reliably based on observed objects and events and not emphasizing feelings or thoughts.

3. The belief of holding mankind to be a "heroic being" and ones own happiness being the one true purpose of life; Productivity and reason being the only absolute.